Comment:
i finished the game weeks ago and here are my thoughts

CONS:
-cringey dialogue
-creepy facial animation
-very predictable story
-the main story is too short
-main character is annoying

PROS:
+really really good graphics (nice colors and everything was well-detailed, every second of the game is wallpaper-worthy)
+very fitting music
+satisfying combat
+big map
+side characters are interesting
+fun missions and side quests

this is worth buying, but i suggest you buy the one that releases on december because its complete with all the dlcs and such

Comment: Dear Guerrilla Games, Thank you for developing such an ambitious and astonishing game like Horizon: Zero Dawn. My friends, my family and I are absolutely amazed by the attention to detail and the vast game world you guys created. However, we all would be more than grateful if you released a small patch which integrates an option to deactivate the permanently visible waypoint marker - and optimally - the loot marker and all other dynamic beacons such as the merchant symbol or green exclamation mark for side quests as well.This little customization option would change the entire game for us!We hope that you'll have an ear for our humble request. Thank you very much, dear developers at Guerrilla Games and keep up your great work! :-)With our best regards,- true supporters of Guerrilla, huge fans of Killzone (now Horizon, as well) and your humble fans -

Title: Horizon Zero Dawn - E3 2016 Gameplay Video | Only on PS4
Comment:
I can't actually believe this, decades since gaming appeared into this world, we finally see a really solid presentation of a 9/10 game with an actual FEMALE (forced) protagonist. This is just wow for me. This is something that we've never seen before. Like, seriously, when was the last time we were able to play as a FEMALE protagonist only? I am not talking about games like Skyrim, Fallout or Mass Effect where we have the option to edit our character, no, those games are out of the picture because they allow us to have both sexes. In this game, the game forces us to play as a female, and a really strong one, not weak-willed

I am really happy with this new direction current generation of gaming.

p.s. this might be one of the very few games that portrait a female character NOT in a sexist way or stripped of any clothes with only few covering her sensual parts. This is just an ordinary gorgeous girl and there wasn't anything sexualised about her. This is actually ground-breaking.

Title: Horizon Zero Dawn - E3 2016 Gameplay Video | Only on PS4
Comment:
Unlike Persona 5 this isn't one of those games that I'd consider buying the console specifically for. Between Skyrim, The Witcher 3 (Yay GOG!), Mad Max, and Shadow of Mordor I've got plenty of similar games to play.

I wish this was coming to the PC because, between that and my 3DS and Vita (Larger storage options are needed but it's a great system aside from that), I get pretty much every game I'm interested in.

I can see not sending it to X-Box, the battle of exclusives would certainly push me towards PlayStation if I was considering a current gen console, but having a game that looks great not come to PC is just sad...

...almost as sad as Atlus not porting any of their great games over.

Title: Horizon Zero Dawn - E3 2016 Gameplay Video | Only on PS4
Comment: not the monsters, not the environment, not the particles effects. The one thing that really caught me in this trailer was the main character. Her movement is just so unbelievably natural and fluid. The animation is so sick and incredible. Y'know how 3rd person games normally have their animation, wherein you have the character running then you release the left stick, and the animation sort of "skips frames" when the character does the standing pose after running? Or when in a running animation you make the character turn and the character leans towards the direction you want it to turn? You don't see that "skip" in animation frames. The transition in different animations and poses is just sooooo seamless and natural. Unbelievable.

Who programmed machines to move and behave exactly like animals? Was that some kind of natural occurrence?

Clearly this is post apocalyptic, but why would guns not exist even primitive ones? There's enough tech to have some kind of ocular tech magic, but not a simple musket?

Color me intrigued.
